=== Baseline evidence: UE-357736 reproduction on Unreal Engine 5.7.4 ===

Source: PIE Output Log from M_Repro.umap, filtered to:
- LogCsvProfiler: iris="..."                  (confirms Iris is enabled or not)
- LogIris: ReplicationSystem ... is created   (confirms Iris init)
- LogNet: ... using replication model ...     (confirms NetDriver chose Iris vs Generic)
- LogTemp: Warning: [Actor] BeginPlay -- Role=N  (per-actor evidence)

Project: 20 instances of AMinimalRepro (zero replicated UPROPERTYs) and
20 instances of AMinimalReproWithState (one UPROPERTY(Replicated) float, no
OnRep). All bReplicates=true with default NetPriority=1.0. Placed in
Content/Maps/M_Repro.umap alongside a PlayerStart and a NavMeshBoundsVolume.
DefaultEngine.ini enables Iris via [SystemSettings] net.Iris.UseIrisReplication=1
plus net.SubObjects.DefaultUseSubObjectReplicationList=1. The Iris plugin is
enabled in IrisLevelPlacedRepro.uproject.

PIE config: Number of Players = 2, Net Mode = Play As Client (so a Dedicated
Server is spawned alongside the 2 clients). Single Process PIE.

Expected (without the bug): Server logs 40 BeginPlay with Role=3 (Authority);
each client logs 40 BeginPlay with Role=1 (SimulatedProxy), totalling 80
Role=1 lines across the 2 client PIE instances.

Observed: Server logs 40/40. Each client logs only a SUBSET (typically 30-32
of 40), leaving 8-10 instances permanently silent (no BeginPlay, no Tick).
Per UE-357736, the silent subset is load-order-dependent.


